# Database Models and Relationships

## Core Models

### User Model
```python
# Located in app/models/models.py
class User:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    email: String (Unique)
    phone: String (Unique)
    full_name: String
    password_hash: String
    role: Enum (USER, AGENT, ADMIN)
    is_active: Boolean
    is_verified: Boolean
    created_at: DateTime
    updated_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    properties: List[Property]  # Properties owned by user
    bookings: List[Booking]     # User's bookings
    visits: List[Visit]        # User's scheduled visits
    swipes: List[Swipe]        # User's swipe actions
    agent_profile: Agent       # Agent profile if role is AGENT
```

### Property Model
```python
class Property:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    title: String
    description: Text
    price: Float
    property_type: Enum (APARTMENT, HOUSE, VILLA, PLOT)
    transaction_type: Enum (SALE, RENT)
    bedrooms: Integer
    bathrooms: Integer
    area_sqft: Float
    location_address: String
    city: String
    state: String
    pincode: String
    latitude: Float
    longitude: Float
    owner_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> User.id)
    agent_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Agent.id)
    is_active: Boolean
    is_verified: Boolean
    created_at: DateTime
    updated_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    owner: User                    # Property owner
    agent: Agent                   # Assigned agent
    amenities: List[Amenity]       # Property amenities
    images: List[PropertyImage]    # Property images
    bookings: List[Booking]        # Property bookings
    visits: List[Visit]           # Property visits
    swipes: List[Swipe]           # Property swipes
```

### Agent Model
```python
class Agent:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    user_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> User.id)
    agency_name: String
    license_number: String
    experience_years: Integer
    specializations: JSON
    service_areas: JSON
    rating: Float
    total_reviews: Integer
    is_verified: Boolean
    created_at: DateTime
    updated_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    user: User                # Agent's user account
    properties: List[Property] # Properties managed by agent
    bookings: List[Booking]    # Bookings through this agent
    visits: List[Visit]       # Visits scheduled by this agent
```

### Booking Model
```python
class Booking:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    user_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> User.id)
    property_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Property.id)
    agent_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Agent.id)
    booking_date: DateTime
    visit_date: DateTime
    status: Enum (PENDING, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, COMPLETED)
    notes: Text
    created_at: DateTime
    updated_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    user: User         # User who made booking
    property: Property # Booked property
    agent: Agent       # Assigned agent
```

### Visit Model
```python
class Visit:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    user_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> User.id)
    property_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Property.id)
    agent_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Agent.id)
    visit_date: DateTime
    visit_time: Time
    status: Enum (SCHEDULED, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED, CANCELLED)
    notes: Text
    feedback: Text
    rating: Integer
    created_at: DateTime
    updated_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    user: User         # User who scheduled visit
    property: Property # Property to visit
    agent: Agent       # Assigned agent
```

### Swipe Model
```python
class Swipe:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    user_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> User.id)
    property_id: UUID (Foreign Key -> Property.id)
    swipe_type: Enum (LIKE, DISLIKE, SUPERLIKE)
    created_at: DateTime

    # Relationships
    user: User         # User who swiped
    property: Property # Swiped property
```

### Amenity Model
```python
class Amenity:
    id: UUID (Primary Key)
    name: String
    category: Enum (BASIC, LUXURY, SECURITY, ENVIRONMENT)
    icon_url: String
    is_active: Boolean

    # Relationships (Many-to-Many with Property)
    properties: List[Property]
```

## Key Relationships

### One-to-One
- `User -> Agent` (when user.role == AGENT)

### One-to-Many
- `User -> Properties` (as owner)
- `Agent -> Properties` (managed properties)
- `User -> Bookings`
- `User -> Visits`
- `User -> Swipes`
- `Property -> Bookings`
- `Property -> Visits`
- `Property -> Swipes`
- `Agent -> Bookings`
- `Agent -> Visits`

### Many-to-Many
- `Property <-> Amenity` (through property_amenities table)

